entries.meaning: The act of pressing an input key; a keypress on a computer keyboard or a typewriter, or a similar input device.

verbs.description: keystroke (third-person singular simple present keystrokes, present participle keystroking, simple past and past participle keystroked)

entries.meaning: To enter (data etc.) by pressing keys on a keyboard.
examples: I keystroked the entire manual, in addition to the keystroking done by the Technical Support and Test groups.
